title: Where 2 Watch: NASCAR TV schedule for Kansas Speedway
text:
Photo by Jonathan Moore/Getty Images FOX Sports Josh Richter - Shake and Bake Crew Share This Story Updated Oct 16, 2015 at 9:29a ET 
The Contender Round continues in the "Sunflower State." 
So you don't miss a second of the action, here's your complete television schedule for Kansas Speedway. 
Friday, Oct. 16 
1 p.m. ET: Sprint Cup Series practice 
2:30 p.m. ET: XFINITY Series practice 
4:30 p.m. ET: XFINITY Series final practice 
6 p.m. ET: Sprint Cup Series qualifying 
8:30 p.m. ET: ARCA Racing Series at Kansas Speedway (FS1) 
10:30 p.m. ET: "FOX Sports Live" (FS1) 
Saturday, Oct. 17 
11:30 a.m. ET: Sprint Cup Series practice 
12:30 p.m. ET: XFINITY Series qualifying 
2:30 p.m. ET: Sprint Cup Series final practice 
4 p.m. ET: XFINITY Series Kansas Lottery 300 
7:30 p.m. ET: "FOX Sports Live" (FS1) 
Sunday, Oct. 18 
11 a.m. ET: "NASCAR RaceDay" (FS1) 
2:15 p.m. ET: Sprint Cup Series Hollywood Casino 400 
11 p.m. ET: "FOX Sports Live" (FS1) 
Midnight: "NASCAR Victory Lane" (FS1) 
FOX Sports GO provides live streaming video of FOX Sports content. Customers of participating video providers may access the live streams through the FOX Sports GO app for iOS devices, as well as on desktops through FOXSportsGO.com .
